summary:
The Security Council,
 Reaffirming the UN Charter and relevant resolutions, particularly 1373 (2001),
 Reaffirming the need to combat terrorist threats to international peace and security,

1. Condemns the Moscow hostage-taking on 23 October 2002 and other recent terrorist acts as threats to international peace and security;
2. Demands immediate and unconditional release of all hostages;
3. Expresses deepest sympathy to the Russian Federation, victims and their families;
4. Urges States to cooperate with Russia to find and bring to justice perpetrators, organizers and sponsors of the terrorist attack, in accordance with resolution 1373 (2001);
5. Expresses determination to combat all forms of terrorism, in accordance with the UN Charter.
